field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"enable-the-activity-reporting-feature\"\u003e\n                        Enable the Activity Reporting Feature\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eAs mentioned earlier, the issue most commonly occurs on devices where the Family Safety Activity reporting feature is disabled. As a heads-up, when this feature is enabled, you will be able to gain insights into your children\u0026#39;s online habits.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eThat said, Microsoft has advised all affected users to enable Activity reporting to temporarily mitigate the problem. To do this, open the Family app on your Windows computer, select your child\u0026#39;s profile, and under the Windows tab, enable the \u0026#34;Activity Reporting\u0026#34; toggle.\u003c/p\u003e    \n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/activity-reporting-toggle-in-the-family-app.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/activity-reporting-toggle-in-the-family-app.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/activity-reporting-toggle-in-the-family-app.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/activity-reporting-toggle-in-the-family-app.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/activity-reporting-toggle-in-the-family-app.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/activity-reporting-toggle-in-the-family-app.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/activity-reporting-toggle-in-the-family-app.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/activity-reporting-toggle-in-the-family-app.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/activity-reporting-toggle-in-the-family-app.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                    \u003cimg width=\"1221\" height=\"319\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Activity Reporting toggle in the Family app.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/activity-reporting-toggle-in-the-family-app.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/activity-reporting-toggle-in-the-family-app.jpg\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e After this, you\u0026#39;ll receive approval requests from your children whenever they try to use Google Chrome. Once you approve their request, they will be able to use the browser without any problems.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"rename-the-chrome-executable-file\"\u003e\n                        Rename the Chrome Executable File\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eAlthough neither Microsoft nor Google recommends this method, many \u003ca href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/chrome/comments/1l2c552/comment/mvt1w2a/?utm_source=share\u0026amp;utm_medium=web3x\u0026amp;utm_name=web3xcss\u0026amp;utm_term=1\u0026amp;utm_content=share_button\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eusers on Reddit have confirmed\u003c/a\u003e that they were able to resolve the issue by renaming the Chrome executable file. Therefore, until a permanent solution becomes available, you can try this workaround as well to fix the problem.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eTo rename the Chrome executable file, open the Start menu, type\u003cstrong\u003e Google Chrome\u003c/strong\u003e in the search bar, right-click Google Chrome, and select \u0026#34;Open File Location.\u0026#34; Then, right-click the Google Chrome shortcut and choose \u0026#34;Open File Location\u0026#34; again.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eNext, right-click the Chrome executable file and select the \u0026#34;Rename\u0026#34; option. Rename it to \u003cstrong\u003echrome1\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e    \n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/renaming-chrome-executable-file-on-windows.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/renaming-chrome-executable-file-on-windows.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/renaming-chrome-executable-file-on-windows.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/renaming-chrome-executable-file-on-windows.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/renaming-chrome-executable-file-on-windows.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/renaming-chrome-executable-file-on-windows.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/renaming-chrome-executable-file-on-windows.jpg?q=70\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=1\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/renaming-chrome-executable-file-on-windows.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/renaming-chrome-executable-file-on-windows.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                    \u003cimg width=\"1002\" height=\"432\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Renaming Chrome executable file on Windows.\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/renaming-chrome-executable-file-on-windows.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/renaming-chrome-executable-file-on-windows.jpg\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e That\u0026#39;s it. This process will bypass the Microsoft Family Safety check, allowing your child to use Google Chrome on the device without any issues.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n                \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"e0cc-4061-8847818281b8\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t\n\t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.howtogeek.com/thanks-to-this-new-feature-i-can-finally-switch-from-chrome-to-firefox-for-good/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/a-podium-with-the-firefox-and-chrome-icons-and-firefox-wearing-a-crown.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/a-podium-with-the-firefox-and-chrome-icons-and-firefox-wearing-a-crown.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/